ossibilities could be reactive hypoglycemia, which is postprandial, but her symptoms are when she misses a meal, so that's more fasting.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04001,0.077796,0.084093,0.088583,0.093043,0.096594,0.097724,0.096897,0.091336,0.089079,0.078758,0.066087],"unified_progress":[0.044528,0.070456,0.081838,0.087886,0.093282,0.097201,0.097956,0.098259,0.094784,0.092912,0.079936,0.060963]},{"section":15,"text":"Also, alcohol abuse can cause hypoglycemia, but the case doesn't mention that.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035054,0.0702,0.080508,0.087407,0.093136,0.098295,0.099478,0.099072,0.094752,0.092291,0.082972,0.066834],"unified_progress":[0.049869,0.076356,0.0829,0.087271,0.092466,0.095103,0.095492,0.097522,0.093447,0.092847,0.078643,0.058084]},{"section":16,"text":"Endocrine issues like adrenal insufficiency can cause hypoglycemia too, but usually with other symptoms like hyperpigmentation, which aren't mentioned here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026099,0.060478,0.075267,0.086389,0.094459,0.09951,0.10491,0.10332,0.09914,0.096783,0.086502,0.067143],"unified_progress":[0.03055,0.060111,0.078644,0.0866,0.096177,0.10179,0.10243,0.10387,0.10111,0.10044,0.082249,0.056021]},{"section":17,"text":"The key here is the Whipple triad: symptoms of hypoglycemia, low glucose level during symptoms, and relief after glucose administration.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037925,0.072559,0.079608,0.084825,0.089647,0.093102,0.095775,0.095188,0.093053,0.091618,0.086699,0.080001],"unified_progress":[0.045855,0.0672,0.077627,0.084993,0.091257,0.097097,0.096775,0.09672,0.094893,0.091351,0.084781,0.071452]},{"section":18,"text":"She fits that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033235,0.069893,0.085407,0.091268,0.093122,0.092179,0.093357,0.092168,0.091077,0.09187,0.084682,0.081741],"unified_progress":[0.057518,0.068374,0.075791,0.084609,0.088065,0.089773,0.091415,0.092663,0.091176,0.093431,0.087567,0.079619]},{"section":19,"text":"Since it's recurrent and fasting-related, insulinoma is a top contender.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034003,0.071194,0.086513,0.091971,0.091265,0.088599,0.089089,0.087479,0.08734,0.090942,0.085121,0.096486],"unified_progress":[0.037034,0.062155,0.072456,0.083149,0.085099,0.087911,0.089987,0.091291,0.093551,0.097376,0.098567,0.10142]},{"section":20,"text":"Let me check if there are other tumors or conditions.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028761,0.062987,0.080817,0.089163,0.094071,0.094788,0.095627,0.095408,0.096037,0.094217,0.087112,0.081012],"unified_progress":[0.036168,0.067273,0.079837,0.092077,0.092853,0.092441,0.095684,0.094778,0.093815,0.097784,0.085915,0.071373]},{"section":21,"text":"Maybe factitious hypoglycemia from someone injecting insulin, but that's less likely without other clues.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029655,0.063073,0.07461,0.083216,0.091166,0.096688,0.10098,0.10213,0.099301,0.097009,0.088972,0.073204],"unified_progress":[0.039089,0.066474,0.078429,0.085099,0.092546,0.096198,0.098,0.10052,0.097998,0.096984,0.083792,0.064868]},{"section":22,"text":"So, putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is insulinoma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031582,0.056456,0.065357,0.071726,0.076146,0.079043,0.08428,0.087343,0.092107,0.097572,0.10398,0.15441],"unified_progress":[0.034969,0.04124,0.049829,0.060776,0.064895,0.074136,0.078924,0.086661,0.094003,0.10317,0.13381,0.17758]},{"section":23,"text":"It's a tumor causing excessive insulin, leading to hypoglycemia when she's not eating.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02855,0.058318,0.067598,0.076715,0.085591,0.092505,0.098375,0.098752,0.098877,0.098712,0.097015,0.098993],"unified_progr